Overview
This project is a dynamic Weather App that allows users to search for weather conditions in cities around the world. The app is designed with a clean and responsive UI, built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, with styling powered by Tailwind CSS. The backend is implemented using PHP, ensuring robust and seamless API integration.

Features
ğŸŒ Search Weather by City: Enter any city's name to get up-to-date weather information.
ğŸŒ¤ï¸ Dynamic City Images: Displays images relevant to the searched city.
ğŸ“ˆ Weather Details: Includes temperature, humidity, wind speed, and weather description.
ğŸ“± Responsive Design: Optimized for desktop and mobile devices.
APIs Used
OpenWeatherMap API
Provides current weather details like temperature, humidity, and wind speed.
Get your API key here: https://openweathermap.org/api

WikiMedia API
Fetches city-specific images and key facts dynamically.
Documentation: https://en.wikipedia.org/api/rest_v1/

Tech Stack
Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Styling: Tailwind CSS
Backend: PHP
APIs: OpenWeatherMap and WikiMedia
How to Run
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy code
git clone <repository-url>
cd <project-folder>
Set up a local server (e.g., using WAMP, XAMPP, or similar tools).
Configure the API keys:
Add your OpenWeatherMap API key to the PHP backend.
No API key is needed for WikiMedia API.
Access the project via the local server (e.g., http://localhost/weather-app).
